.SH "NAME"
make_bad_inode \- mark an inode bad due to an I/O error
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'void\ make_bad_inode('u
.BI "void make_bad_inode(struct\ inode\ *\ " "inode" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIinode\fR
.RS 4
Inode to mark bad
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
When an inode cannot be read due to a media or remote network failure this function makes the inode
\(lqbad\(rq
and causes I/O operations on it to fail from this point on\&.
